description:
The URL masking hook in src/lib/analytics.js (maskUrl() called from buildEnvelope()) accepts regex patterns but is never fed any. The docs site currently doesn't have sensitive per-user paths, so this is premature.

Add masks to window.vbAnalyticsConfig.urlMasks when the site grows paths like /admin/<user-id>/, /preview/<draft-id>/, or similar. Config shape:

  window.vbAnalyticsConfig = {
    urlMasks: [
      { pattern: /^\/admin\/[^/]+/, replace: '/admin/*' },
      { pattern: /^\/preview\/[0-9a-f]{8,}/, replace: '/preview/*' },
    ],
  };

Scope: not urgent. Close if/when the docs site grows such paths, or file a broader "analytics privacy review" issue.

Reference: admin/r-n-d/analytics/analytics-spec.md "URL Masking" section.
